Job Responsibility:

1. Design and build applications for the iOS platform

2. Ensure the performance, quality, and responsiveness of applications

3. Collaborate with the product team to define, design, and ship new features. Identify and correct bottlenecks and fix bugs

4. Help maintain code quality, organization, and automatization

Job Requirements:

1. 3+ years of native iOS development experience;

2. Good understanding of software development principles, capabilities, and limitations of iOS platform;

3. Proficiency in Objective-C or Swift;

Job Responsibility:

1. Design, implement the new-user features of our mobile application;

2. Collaborate with the design and product teams to create a world-class mobile experience;

3. Optimize mobile applications on the Android platforms;

Job Requirements:

1. 3+ years of native Android development experience;

2. Strong knowledge of Java/Kotlin, Android frameworks, and mobile trends

3. Passion for building great mobile app experiences

Job Responsibility:

1. Collaborate with product managers to develop high-quality audio and video related new features aligned with business needs;

2. Participate in the development of Android Audio and Video SDK in the multimedia platform, including short video shooting, recording, image editing, and other related fields;

3. Responsible for research on new technologies in the Audio and Video fields and implementation in Audio and Video SDK.

Job Requirements:
- Experiences in platforms: Web, Android, and IOS

Job Responsibility：
- Help improve the whole lifecycle of services from design, operation to refinement;
- Support services by consulting system design, developing software platforms and frameworks, planning capacity, and launching reviews;

Job Requirements:
- Experience in designing, analyzing, and troubleshooting large-scale distributed systems;
- Experience with network software, including TCP/IP, IP Tables, NAT, Deep Packet Inspection, IPV4, IPV6, routing protocols, etc;
- Bachelor or above degree in Computer Science or related technical background with 1+ years of software/system engineering, or equivalent working experience;

As a Data Scientist on FIX team, you will havethe unique opportunity for massive impact given that you’ll directly drive projects that can reduce cost, improve user experience and stimulate sustainable growth. You’ll influence key strategic decisions across all Airbnb product teams by bringing customer feedback data and insights to the table. You'll be in the driver seat to change Airbnb’s DNA around defect reduction using data to drive forward our vision of a world where guests and hosts can use our products seamlessly. 

Responsibilities include:

Defining, tracking and explaining key metrics across all surface areas;
Creating and empowering a company-wide measurement and attribution framework on Community Support contacts;
Quantifying long-term impact of Community Support contacts and trade-off against other goals;
Consolidating all customer feedback channel data and driving insights;
